Monitoring is a critical component of any DevOps strategy. Today, I want to share a list of GitHub repositories that have helped me with DevOps monitoring:

Prometheus - https://lnkd.in/dSc7pumr
Prometheus is an open-source monitoring system that collects metrics from monitored targets and stores them in a time-series database.

Grafana - https://lnkd.in/dZQVYGjj
Grafana is an open-source platform for monitoring and analyzing metrics and logs from various sources.

ELK Stack - https://lnkd.in/dZpSEkYM
The ELK Stack is a set of open-source tools consisting of Elasticsearch, Logstash, and Kibana, used for centralizing and analyzing logs.

Telegraf - https://lnkd.in/dwBFVR3s
Telegraf is a plugin-driven server agent for collecting and reporting metrics.

InfluxDB - https://lnkd.in/dCjp62pf
InfluxDB is an open-source time-series database that is optimized for high-performance storage and retrieval of time-series data.

Zabbix - https://lnkd.in/dmDxd7sE
Zabbix is an open-source monitoring solution that can monitor servers, network devices, and applications.

Nagios - https://lnkd.in/dW-QCSWb
Nagios is a powerful monitoring system that can monitor hosts, services, and network devices

Icinga - https://lnkd.in/dCPy2EuF
Icinga is an open-source monitoring system that can monitor hosts, services, and network devices.

Sensu - https://lnkd.in/dzmB9fEh
Sensu is a monitoring and automation platform that can monitor infrastructure, applications, and services.

Jaeger - https://lnkd.in/dycc_VRd
Jaeger is an open-source distributed tracing system used for monitoring and troubleshooting microservices-based distributed systems.
